<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="234" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1112]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Boppré" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Zerny" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[322,490,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Gloora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[322,490,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Gloora sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily confused with some 
<taxonomicName box="[825,937,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lithosiini">Lithosiini</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName box="[1061,1134,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1061,1134,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Agylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Druce (Hoffmann 1936)" authorityName="Druce (Hoffmann" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cyptonychia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviceps">
<emphasis box="[1188,1435,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Cyptonychia flaviceps</emphasis>
Druce (
<bibRefCitation box="[234,417,1124,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" refId="ref7410" refString="Hoffmann, F. (1936) Beitrage zur Lepidopterenfauna von Sta. Catharina. Syntomidae. Entomologische Rundschau, 53 (31), 435 - 439." type="journal article">Hoffmann 1936</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<bibRefCitation box="[199,559,1159,1184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" refId="ref7662" refString="Pinheiro, L. R. &amp; Gaal-Haszler, S. (2015) Illustrated catalogue of Neotropical Ctenuchina, Euchromiina and Pericopina types (Lepidoptera, Erebidae, Arctiinae, Arctiini) described by Hans Zerny, with discussion on their taxonomic status. Zootaxa, 3925 (4), 505 - 535. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3925.4.2" type="journal article">Pinheiro &amp; Gaal-Haszler (2015)</bibRefCitation>
asserted that the habitus and genitalia are certainly not part of a monophyletic concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1819" box="[276,382,1197,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Eucereon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,382,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Eucereon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also mentioning that the species may be related to 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1389,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Hyaleucerea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="mundula" variety="alba">
<emphasis box="[964,1211,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Hyaleucerea mundula</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1225,1389,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Eucereon alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,266,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Theages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestalis">
<emphasis box="[151,266,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">E. vestalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With the last two they share similarities in the color of adults males and females. Greater similarities in relation to external morphology and genitalia are found with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Boppré" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Boppré" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[899,1038,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Hyaleucerea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mundula">
<emphasis box="[899,1038,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">H. mundula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1107,1194,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Eucereon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[1107,1194,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">E. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1892" box="[1264,1386,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Theages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestalis">
<emphasis box="[1264,1386,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">E. vestalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see Discussion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="234" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zerny" authorityYear="1931" box="[199,420,1341,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Eucereon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeum">
<emphasis box="[199,420,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Eucereon sericeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently erroneously transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" box="[1042,1343,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agaraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1042,1138,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Agaraea</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer
</taxonomicName>
, [1855] (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,475,1376,1400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" refId="ref6497" refString="Beccacece, H. M. &amp; Zapata, A. I. (2017) Taxonomic changes of some neotropical species of Arctiini Leach (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae). Zootaxa, 4272 (3), 421 - 429. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4272.3.7" type="journal article">Beccacece &amp; Zapata (2017)</bibRefCitation>
which belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.F.Kirby" authorityYear="1892" box="[727,891,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Phaegopterina">Phaegopterina</taxonomicName>
. The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1090,1186,1376,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agaraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1186,1376,1399]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Agaraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="8" pageNumber="234" refId="ref6497" refString="Beccacece, H. M. &amp; Zapata, A. I. (2017) Taxonomic changes of some neotropical species of Arctiini Leach (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae). Zootaxa, 4272 (3), 421 - 429. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4272.3.7" type="journal article">Beccacece &amp; Zapata (2017: figs. 11‒14)</bibRefCitation>
are very different and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zerny" authorityYear="1931" box="[620,753,1413,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Eucereon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeum">
<emphasis box="[620,753,1413,1436]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">E. sericeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Boppré" authorityYear="2018" box="[805,936,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Ctenuchina">Ctenuchina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
